        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} this time for the first time overnight. And not by chance, but with deliberate. In fact, we call there every time before. Why? Quite simply: rosin braid. And not just any, but the only true, still warm and slightly Klitschy rosin braid on the inside, as you still know it from GDR times-freshly baked at the baker in the Kaufland. </p>
        <p> We had actually pre -ordered two pieces. In the end it became four - you know each other. Care for the next few days. Because once you have this perfect mix of soft, juicy and crispy, you don't want to go back. Clearly for us: a culinary mandatory date. </p>
        <p> From there it was only around 30 minutes to the Tropical Islands - the long -awaited wellness weekend could start. The parking space was already reserved, so quickly turned off the motorhome, powered, moved, moved, packed bags and off with the shuttle into the hall. And it was already there: the feeling of pure vacation. Here the watch simply ticks differently - or rather, it doesn't matter. No view of opening times or weather apps. Only relaxation. </p>
        <p> Our first goal: the sauna area. We immediately arrived between warmth, steam and tropical vegetation in &ldquo;vacation mode&rdquo;. For three days we let ourselves go - swim, walk, doze, read, read. Everything without a hurry, without pressure. This is how relaxation feels. </p>

