        <p> Of course there were also things that were less relaxing - such as the now clearly grown population of so -called rainforest cockroaches. Once we were even surrounded "friendly" in the evening, which moved us to visit the rest of the stay rather illuminated corners. Sure, they are part of the Halle ecosystem, but after the long Corona closing time, these little roommates had made themselves quite wide-literally. Creepy? Yes. Takes some getting used to? In any case. </p>
