        <p> The next morning it went back home - without long breaks, because the traffic played along and we got through well. Only the bare essentials were unloaded at home. The rest could wait, because first there was a visit to the Ahrensburg wine festival - a small, relaxed end of our vacation. For dinner we went into time, before the big one finally started and washing the laundry. </p>
